Yes, you're right that you can check taostats and sort by incentive and if you're near the bottom (not counting validators and miners in immunity), then those are the next miners that will be de-registered. You can also cross reference miner UID's from the dashboards with how they're performing on taostats to see what kind of scores get what kind of incentives. When we first started this subnet, we wanted it to be easy to mine for anyone new to mining in Bittensor. In the last 6 months since we launched, the mining has become incredibly competitive (as is the case with basically every subnet these days) and miners are finding the best ways to provide the best services and even as owners, we don't necessarily know what all the miners are doing. We run tests and such on our end to ensure miners are not doing anything sketchy to artificially boost their scores without providing proper services. So to mine our subnet or any subnet, it's the role of the miners to figure out the best setups that will keep your miner alive while also being profitable. As a metaphor, the subnet owners write the rules for how to play the game and the miners are playing the game.
